          h1.divide-section Buttons

          p  Really cool and simple CSS3 buttons to give your application a smooth feel.

          table.bordered
            thead
              tr
                th Button
                th Class
                th Description
            tbody
              tr
                td
                  button(href="#" ,class="button") Default Button
                td
                 code button
                td Standard gray button with gradient
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button primary") Primary Button
                td
                 code button primary
                td Provides extra visual weight and identifies the primary action in a set of buttons
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button info") Info Button
                td
                 code button info
                td Used as an alternative to the default styles
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button positive") Positive Button
                td
                 code button positive
                td Indicates a positive action

              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button success") Success Button
                td
                 code button success
                td Indicates a successful action  
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button warning") Warning Button
                td
                 code button warning
                td Indicates caution should be taken with this action
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button negative") Danger Button
                td
                 code button negative
                td Indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action
              
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button dark") Dark Button
                td
                 code button dark
                td Alternate dark gray button, not tied to a semantic action or use
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button disabled") Disabled Button
                td
                 code button disabled
                td Describe a disabled button  
              tr
                td
                 button(href="#" ,class="button pill") Disabled Button
                td
                 code button pill
                td Creates pill button   
              

          h2 Size modifiers
          p
            | Add the 
            code .button-mini
            |  , 
            code .button-small
            |  or 
            code .button-large
            |  class to a button to make it smaller or larger.
          
          .preview-box
            p
              button.button.mini(type='button') Mini button
              button.button.mini.primary(type='button') Primary Mini button
            p
              button.button.small(type='button') Small button
              button.button.small.primary(type='button') Primary Small button
            p
              button.button(type='button',class="button") 
                | Default button
                
              button.button.primary(type='button')
                | Primary button
                
            p
              button.button.large(type='button') Large button
              button.button.large.primary(type='button') Primary Large button

            p
              button.button.massive(type='button') Massive button
              button.button.massive.primary(type='button') Primary Massive button 
          
          h2 Icons 
          p
            | Add the 
            code .button-mini
            |  , 
            code .button-small
            |  or 
            code .button-large
            |  class to a button to make it smaller or larger.
          
          .preview-box
            h3 Add icon to button
            p 
              | Add i tag as 
              code= "<i class='icon-name'></i> e.g. <i class='i-bull-horn'></i>"

            p
              button.button(type='button')
                | Default button
                i.i-Bull-horn    
              button.button.primary(type='button')
                | Primary button
                i.i-Bull-horn 
            h3 Add icon as box  
            p 
              | Add icon in box 
              code= "<button class='button box'> Default Button <i class='i-bull-horn'></i></button>"

            p
              button.button(type='button',class="button box") 
                | Default button
                i.i-Bull-horn 
              button.button.primary(type='button',class="button box") 
                | Primary button
                i.i-Bull-horn   

            h3 Change icon direction with box  
            p 
              | There are two option left and right. default is right so we don't need to mention it.

            p
              button.button.primary(type='button',class="button box") 
                | Primary button
                i.i-Bull-horn  
            p 
              | To change box direction to left side. Just add <code>left</code> class as following code  
            p  
              code= "<button class='button box left'> Default Button <i class='i-bull-horn'></i></button>"
            p
              button.button.primary.left(type='button',class="button box") 
                | Primary button
                i.i-Bull-horn

          h2 Button Groups
          p 
            | You can create button groups in two ways 
          
            
          h3 
            | Wrap inside a container 
            span.text-small.text-muted Easy way
          
          p 
            | Just wrap inside 
            code buttons-group
            |  and add 
            code button
            |  to every button inside stack.

          .preview-box
            p.buttons-group
              a(href="#",class="button ") Left button
              a(href="#",class="button ") Middle button
              a(href="#",class="button ") Middle button
              a(href="#",class="button ") Right button 

          h3 Use classes 
          p 
            | Mention classes  
            code group-left
            |  for leftmost button and 
            code group-middle 
            |  for all Middle buttons and finish with 
            code group-right 

          .preview-box
            p
              a(href="#",class="button group-left") Left button
              a(href="#",class="button group-middle") Middle button
              a(href="#",class="button group-right") Right button        

            p
              a(href="#",class="button group-left") Left button
              a(href="#",class="button group-middle") Middle button
              a(href="#",class="button group-middle") Middle button
              a(href="#",class="button group-right") Right button  

                    

